'''Adam M. Casey''' is a former Division 1 college football player for the [[University of Missouri]],<ref name="ABC 17 News">{{cite web|last1=Kauffman|first1=Andrew|title=Former MU football player pushes forward for 'her'|url=http://www.abc17news.com/sports/former-mu-football-player-pushes-forward-for-her/612835763|publisher=ABC 17 News|accessdate=15 January 2018}}</ref> [[U.S. Marine]] Infantry Officer, [[cancer survivor]]<ref name="The Blaze">{{cite web|last1=Hoilman|first1=Carly|title=‘I Don’t Fear Death Anymore’: Former Marine Who Survived Stage 4 Cancer Shares How He Lives and Loves Without Reservations|url=https://www.theblaze.com/news/2016/04/27/i-dont-fear-death-anymore-former-marine-who-survived-stage-4-cancer-shares-how-he-lives-and-loves-without-reservations|publisher=The Blaze|accessdate=15 January 2018}}</ref> and founder of the non-profit '''''I Do It For Her'''''. He is a [[TEDx]] speaker<ref name="Ted">{{cite web|title=Theme: Shaping the Future: The Power of a Single Idea|url=https://www.ted.com/tedx/events/16968|publisher=Ted|accessdate=15 January 2018}}</ref> who uses his non-profit to encourage others to take risks to become their best selves. ''I Do It For Her'' provides scholarships to at-risk youth in the [[St. Louis]] area<ref name="This Is Insider">{{cite web|last1=Lakritz|first1=Talia|title=After kicking cancer, this former Marine celebrated by racing over 10,000 miles across Europe and Asia|url=http://www.thisisinsider.com/cancer-survivor-marine-raced-mongol-rally-2016-12#he-hopes-to-motivate-others-to-take-risks-to-become-their-best-selves-just-as-the-organizations-namesake-did-for-him-18|publisher=This Is Insider|accessdate=15 January 2018}}</ref> and wish-granting resources to help people to accomplish their dreams.<ref name="Circuit of Success">{{cite web|title=Casey, along with Jason Klarfeld, founded the I Do It For Her Foundation in 2012.|url=http://www.circuitofsuccess.com/2017/03/20/adam-casey-joins-show/|publisher=Circuit of Success|accessdate=15 January 2018}}</ref>

