[[File:Adolph Woermann.jpg|thumb|Adolph Woermann]]
'''Adolph Woermann''' (10 December 1847 in [[Hamburg]] – 4 May 1911 in the [[Grönwohld]]-Hof near [[Trittau]]) was a German merchant, shipowner and politician, who was also instrumental in the establishment of [[German colonial empire|German colonies]] in [[Africa]]. In his time he was the largest German trader to West Africa<ref name="Bade-362">Klaus J. Bade: [http://www.imis.uni-osnabrueck.de/BadeFabri.pdf ''Friedrich Fabri und der Imperialismus in der Bismarckzeit. Revolution – Depression – Expansion.''] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719110657/http://www.imis.uni-osnabrueck.de/BadeFabri.pdf |date=19 July 2011 }} Freiburg i.Br. 1975, 2005 (2005 mit neuem Vorwort: Osnabrück), S. 362 (retrieved 23 November 2006)</ref> and – with his [[Woermann-Linie]] – the largest private shipowner in the world.<ref name="Bade-315">Klaus J. Bade: [http://www.imis.uni-osnabrueck.de/BadeFabri.pdf ''Friedrich Fabri und der Imperialismus in der Bismarckzeit. Revolution – Depression – Expansion.''] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719110657/http://www.imis.uni-osnabrueck.de/BadeFabri.pdf |date=19 July 2011 }} Freiburg i.Br. 1975, 2005 (2005 mit neuem Vorwort: Osnabrück), S. 315 (retrieved 23 November 2006)</ref>

