Engineer '''Francisco Escárcega Márquez''' (died 1938) was a builder of [[railroad]]s in [[Mexico]] and fought in the [[Mexican Revolution]]. He was born in [[Tlaxcala, Tlaxcala]], and opened up areas in southern and eastern Mexico with railways. The city and municipality of [[Escárcega]] in the state of [[Campeche]] are named after him.


