'''Madhav Bhattarai''' ({{lang-ne|माधव भट्टराई}}) is a Nepalese writer and academic. He is chairman of the Nepal committee of [[astrologer]]s. He earned his PhD in [[Sanskrit]] literature. He writes in Sanskrit and [[Nepali language|Nepali]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usnepalonline.com/archives/news_pandit_narayanprasad_pokhrel_religious_martyr_june15_08.htm|title=Nepalese News Live from the capital of the world-New York City|website=Usnepalonline.com|accessdate=29 November 2017}}</ref> 

== Career ==
He worked a "Nayab Badaguruji", appointed by late king [[Birendra Bir Bikram Shah Dev]]. 

Beginning in March, 2005 Bhattarai served as a president of Nepal Panchanga Nirnayak Samiti. 

Bhattarai founded academic organizations and co-founded Nepal Sikshya Campus (College of Education), [[Kathmandu]]. He worked as a chief of Balmiki Campus located at Kathmandu. 

