{{Expand Hungarian|Szőr Péter|date=December 2013}} {{Infobox person | name = Péter Szőr | image = | caption = | birth_name = Péter Szőr | birth_date = {{birth date|1970|7|17|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Balatonfüred]], [[Veszprém County]], [[Hungary]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2013|11|12|1970|7|17|df=yes}} | death_place = California | other_names = | alma_mater = [[University of Pannonia]] | occupation = Computer virus and security researcher, entrepreneur, author | years_active = 1990–2013 | spouse = Natalia Nemeth | children = Daniel Szor | imagesize = }}
'''Péter Szőr''' (17 July 1970 – 12 November 2013) was a [[Hungarian people|Hungarian]] computer virus and security researcher, entrepreneur and author.
Born in [[Balatonfüred]], [[Veszprém County]], Szőr began an interest in [[computer virus]]es in 1990. A [[University of Pannonia]] graduate, he authored several virus-related books, and was renowned for his work. From 2009 until his death, he worked for a [[McAfee]] antivirus firm working on a new solution to stop viruses.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.peterszor.com/aboutus.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050204050946/http://peterszor.com/aboutus.html |dead-url=yes |archive-date=February 4, 2005 |title=About Péter Szőr |publisher=peterszor.com |accessdate=December 10, 2013 }}</ref>
In Early 1999, Péter Szőr had a son, Daniel Szőr, with his spouse Natalia Nemeth.
In May 2014, Virus Bulletin introduced the Péter Szőr Award to be given annually in recognition of the best piece of technical security research done that year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.virusbulletin.com/blog/2014/05/announces-p-ter-sz-r-award |title=Virus Bulletin announces Péter Ször Award |publisher=virusbulletin.com |date=May 23, 2014 |accessdate=September 29, 2018 }}</ref> Péter Szőr died on 12 November 2013, aged 43.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://index.hu/tech/2013/11/13/elhunyt_szor_peter/|title=Meghalt Szőr Péter|publisher=index.hu|language=hu|accessdate=December 10, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.mcafee.com/mcafee-labs/in-memory-of-peter-szor|title=In Memory of Peter Szor|date=November 16, 2013|publisher=blogs.mcafee.com|accessdate=December 10, 2013}}</ref>
